The paper deals with a signal processing problem of direction finding in partly calibrated arrays, which is a common topic in the field of information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), and machine learning (cs.LG) among others. The proposed method involves the use of mixed nuclear norm and $\ell_1$ norm minimization, which are commonly used in compressed sensing (cs.SI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, these five categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
